## App Market setup required

This template includes App Market readiness checks in the dashboard, but Wix Dev Center configuration is still required before submission:

1. Set the real app namespace and create app data collections with IDs like `<app-namespace>/SyncProfiles`, `<app-namespace>/ProductMappings`, and `<app-namespace>/AuditLogs`.
2. Configure only the minimum Stores permissions listed in the Settings & billing tab.
3. Keep both Wix Stores Catalog V1 and V3 code paths. Always call `catalogVersioning.getCatalogVersion()` before product, inventory, collection, or category operations.
4. Configure paid tiers through Wix Billing. Do not link to external checkout for app plan upgrades.
5. Complete Etsy OAuth on the backend and store secrets/tokens in Wix Secrets Manager or encrypted backend storage.
6. Handle app-instance identity and `originInstanceId` for copied sites during production lifecycle provisioning.
7. Run install, typecheck, build, Wix preview, browser checks, listing metadata, privacy policy, support contact, and console-error validation before App Market review.

## Design system

The dashboard uses a custom **Sapphire Precision** design system (`src/dashboard/styles/sapphire.css`) by design, not `@wix/design-system` components. It is still wrapped in the standard Wix provider stack in `src/dashboard/withProviders.tsx` (`WixDesignSystemProvider` with `newColorsBranding` + `i18n.getLocale()`, and `@wix/design-system/styles.global.css` imported before the Sapphire styles), so the app inherits Wix theming and locale while keeping its custom look.